criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Healthy adults 20-75 years of age;

          -  Body weight higher than 110 pounds;

          -  BMI below 35;

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Previous major gastrointestinal surgery (absorption of test product may be altered)
             (minor surgery not a problem);

          -  Currently taking daily OTC medications, such as NSAIDs, Tylenol, allergy medications,
             and others (birth control and 81 mg aspirin not a problem);

          -  Taking medications that affect the mind (such as anti-depressants) or nervous system
             (such as gabapentin);

          -  Currently experiencing intense stressful events and life changes;

          -  Actively depressed;

          -  Experiencing sleep disturbances;

          -  Working night shift;

          -  Pregnant, nursing, or trying to become pregnant;

          -  Food intolerances or allergies currently causing discomfort (such as Celiac's
             disease), due to ongoing inflammatory reactions that may negatively affect product
             absorption within the 3 hours of testing;

          -  Food allergies related to ingredients in test product.
